{"parse":{"title":"Hardy's Well","pageid":51276953,"revid":835643896,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Hardy%27s_Well_2016_002.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b3/Hardy%27s_Well_2016_002.jpg/220px-Hardy%27s_Well_2016_002.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"165\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b3/Hardy%27s_Well_2016_002.jpg/330px-Hardy%27s_Well_2016_002.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b3/Hardy%27s_Well_2016_002.jpg/440px-Hardy%27s_Well_2016_002.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"4032\" data-file-height=\"3024\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Hardy%27s_Well_2016_002.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Hardy's Well, Manchester</div></div></div>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Wall_poem_and_pub_tables,_Wilmslow_Road,_Manchester_-_geograph.org.uk_-_1393195.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e2/Wall_poem_and_pub_tables%2C_Wilmslow_Road%2C_Manchester_-_geograph.org.uk_-_1393195.jpg/220px-Wall_poem_and_pub_tables%2C_Wilmslow_Road%2C_Manchester_-_geograph.org.uk_-_1393195.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"165\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e2/Wall_poem_and_pub_tables%2C_Wilmslow_Road%2C_Manchester_-_geograph.org.uk_-_1393195.jpg/330px-Wall_poem_and_pub_tables%2C_Wilmslow_Road%2C_Manchester_-_geograph.org.uk_-_1393195.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e2/Wall_poem_and_pub_tables%2C_Wilmslow_Road%2C_Manchester_-_geograph.org.uk_-_1393195.jpg/440px-Wall_poem_and_pub_tables%2C_Wilmslow_Road%2C_Manchester_-_geograph.org.uk_-_1393195.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"640\" data-file-height=\"480\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Wall_poem_and_pub_tables,_Wilmslow_Road,_Manchester_-_geograph.org.uk_-_1393195.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Lemn Sissay's poem on the side of the pub</div></div></div>\n<p><b>Hardy's Well</b> is a <a href=\"/wiki/Public_house\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Public house\">public house</a> located at the end of the <a href=\"/wiki/Curry_Mile\" title=\"Curry Mile\">Curry Mile</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-MEN_8Aug2016_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-MEN_8Aug2016-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> at 257 <a href=\"/wiki/Wilmslow_Road\" title=\"Wilmslow Road\">Wilmslow Road</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-WhatPub_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-WhatPub-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> in <a href=\"/wiki/Rusholme\" title=\"Rusholme\">Rusholme</a>, south <a href=\"/wiki/Manchester\" title=\"Manchester\">Manchester</a>, near to <a href=\"/wiki/Platt_Fields_Park\" title=\"Platt Fields Park\">Platt Fields Park</a>. The 200-year-old building is named after <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Hardy%27s_Brewery&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Hardy&#39;s Brewery (page does not exist)\">Hardy's Brewery</a>, and was formerly known as <b>Birch Villa</b>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-MEN_8Aug2016_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-MEN_8Aug2016-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> later the <b>Birch Villa Hotel</b>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-heritagestatement_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-heritagestatement-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> which has existed on the site since 1837. The front of the building has a Hardy's mosaic on it,<sup id=\"cite_ref-WhatPub_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-WhatPub-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> and is two storeys high with three bays, built of red brick.<sup id=\"cite_ref-heritagestatement_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-heritagestatement-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Following from a conversation between <a href=\"/wiki/Lemn_Sissay\" title=\"Lemn Sissay\">Lemn Sissay</a> and the landlord in 1994, it has one of the first <a href=\"/wiki/Public_art\" title=\"Public art\">public poems</a> written on one of its gable walls. The poem is known as \"Hardy's Well\", after the name of the pub.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Sissay104_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Sissay104-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> Sissay went on to display poetry UK-wide.<sup id=\"cite_ref-MEN_8Aug2016_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-MEN_8Aug2016-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>It was a popular venue for <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Manchester\" title=\"University of Manchester\">University of Manchester</a> students, and of <a href=\"/wiki/Manchester_City_F.C.\" title=\"Manchester City F.C.\">Manchester City F.C.</a> fans when the club was based at <a href=\"/wiki/Maine_Road\" title=\"Maine Road\">Maine Road</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-MEN_8Aug2016_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-MEN_8Aug2016-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>It is owned by <a href=\"/wiki/Enterprise_Inns\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Enterprise Inns\">Enterprise Inns</a>. It was listed as an <a href=\"/wiki/Asset_of_community_value\" title=\"Asset of community value\">Asset of community value</a> in 2015 as a result of an application by the <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Rusholme_%26_Fallowfield_Civic_Society&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Rusholme &amp; Fallowfield Civic Society (page does not exist)\">Rusholme &amp; Fallowfield Civic Society</a>. The pub closed in July 2016,<sup id=\"cite_ref-MEN_8Aug2016_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-MEN_8Aug2016-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> and is at risk of being demolished.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Sissay7Aug2016_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Sissay7Aug2016-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> A planning application by <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Eamar_Development&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Eamar Development (page does not exist)\">Eamar Development</a> to turn it into flats and shops was submitted in 2018, which would see the shell of the pub incorporated into a larger building, with the poem on the wall as part of the inside of the foyer as well as replicated on the new building's outside wall. The new building would be 6 storeys tall,<sup id=\"cite_ref-MEN_20Mar18_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-MEN_20Mar18-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> and contain 62 flats<sup id=\"cite_ref-heritagestatement_3-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-heritagestatement-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> with shops on the ground floor.<sup id=\"cite_ref-MEN_20Mar18_6-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-MEN_20Mar18-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Hardy%27s_Well&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist columns references-column-width\" style=\"-moz-column-width: 40em; -webkit-column-width: 40em; column-width: 40em; list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-MEN_8Aug2016-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-MEN_8Aug2016_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-MEN_8Aug2016_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-MEN_8Aug2016_1-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-MEN_8Aug2016_1-3\"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-MEN_8Aug2016_1-4\"><sup><i><b>e</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/whats-on/hardys-well-curry-mile-closed-11717209\">\"Hardy's Well pub is shut down\"</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/Manchester_Evening_News\" title=\"Manchester Evening News\">M